50|$|Like {{other large}} {{primitive}} temnospondyls, <b>Eryops</b> would have grown slowly and gradually from aquatic larvae, {{but they did}} not go through a dramatic metamorphosis like many modern amphibians. While adults probably lived in ponds and rivers, or may have ventured onto their banks, juvenile <b>Eryops</b> may have lived in swamps, which may have offered more shelter from predators.|$|E
